choices.text:
There are three killers in a room. Someone enters the room and kills one of them. Nobody leaves the room. How many killers are left in the room?
If there were initially more than one killer in the room, then after one is killed, there would still be at least one killer left in the room. If there was only one killer in the room and they did not leave, then there would still be one killer left. Therefore, the answer depends on the initial number of killers in the room.
